e middle row arts childhood hero art looked up to an african american baseball player by the name of cumberland posey he even played with him on a baseball team which was very odd for the time rooney and the nfl trying to get a team one huge problem that stood in arts way was the blue laws the blue laws prohibited any commerical entertainment which was the only day avaliable for pro football someone on the enemy lines arts brother jim was a state senator jim was trying to get the blue laws modified in order to have football on sundaysthey almost had a done deal when jim got into a horrible crash and was in a coma for a few days the nfl takes root summer nfl owner convention at the fort pitt hotel they welcomed  new membersthe new members were art rooeny from the pittsburgh pirates bert bell from the philidelphia eagles and the new cardinals owner charles bidwell contributions to the nfl the orignal owners they divided the leauge in to two fiveteam divisions the winners would meet in a championship gamethey allowed passing from anywhere behind the line of scrimmagethe goal posts were moved foward to make kicking field goals easierthey also changed the football shape to make it easier to throw starting a franchise from nothing art had a lot of problems finding a stadiumuniversity of pittsburgh refused to let them use their stadium until the owner of the pittbsburgh pirates let him use forbes field in the fall of  the first season a vision of what is to come uniforms and logos their season one record was wlt within their next ten years they finall make it to the playoffs in they were horrible in the beginning in their first ten years they lost or tied  of  games after going to the playoffs in  they did not go to the playoffs for another  years the draft art rooney and bert bell were tired of betting wars over college prospects leauge meeting rooney and bell decided to bring up tht issue afterward all of the owners initited the draft the war and combinations wars caused a lot of teams to combine  seasonworld war ii  the steelers temporaily combined with the eagles to become the steagles seasonworld war ii the steelers temporaily combined with the chicago cardinals to become cardpitt changing names  to arts team was called the pittsburgh pirates  the pittsburgh pirates became the pittsburgh steelers to better fit the nickname of pittsburghsteel city and recreate the teamthe name change didnt affect the way the team played the same old steelers the players they drafted were begging to be tradedjoe greenes first season as a steeler was he even threatened to leave football rooneys place of refuge shamrock farms a small farm in virgina was art rooneys refuge from football and the city football not his only venture rooneymcginely boxing club was a huge part of arts life if the nfl team didnt work this was his fallback the rooney twins kidnapped august   the cheif got a ransom note saying that he had to leave  under a park bench if he valued his twin sons lifeseptember  he got a more ominous note and he follwed the instructions the fbi watched the bench and it ended up being young teenage girls impact on civil rights he fired a coach bill austin austin had some issues but a main issue was his problem with african americansconstruction of three rivers stadium art made sure that there were african american union workers bulding it a decade of change in order of apperence jack lambert mean joe greene art the cheif rooney and terry bradshaw the s brought a new faith to the pittsburgh steelers and art rooney and the only years in the s that the steelers did not make a playoff appearence  new recruits  meanjoe greenedt first round terry bradshawqb st round jack hamlbnd roundfranco harrisrbst roundjack lambertlb nd round the steel curtain  mean joe greene  defensive tackle   l c greenwood  defensive end   ernie holmes  defensive tackle – dwight white  defensive end – mel blount cornerback  jack lambert linebacker  jack ham linebacker  they won 